KEYWORD: Drug Involvement and Substance Abuse

DIGEST: Applicant engaged in moderate marijuana use over a lengthy period of time before applying for a security clearance. He used marijuana to cope with anxiety disorder. With professional and faith-based help, he learned to cope with his anxiety disorder and has not used marijuana for 20 months. Applicant submitted a favorable comprehensive substance abuse evaluation, made significant lifestyle changes, and executed a signed statement of intent not to use drugs with automatic revocation of clearance for any violation. Clearance is granted.

